DOC.TEXT:
   Here is the 54-37 vote by which the Senate on
Tuesday refused to limit debate on a broad anti-crime bill.
   The vote fell six short of the 60 required to invoke
debate-limiting cloture. A ``yes'' vote was to limit debate; a
``no'' vote was against a limitation.
   Voting ``yes'' were 44 Democrats and 10 Republicans.
   Voting ``no'' were 6 Democrats and 31 Republicans.
   xxx denotes senators not voting.
